Family 
<taxonomicName id="D9F54D6B1E5C564F9F42906A8A92FDF4" authorityName="Grey" authorityYear="1825" box="[828,1222,512,599]" class="Mammalia" family="Otariidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="0" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">OTARIIDAE</taxonomicName>
(EARED SEALS)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="56EF65631E5C564F988F90CF8610FC9F" pageId="0" pageNumber="34" type="description">
<paragraph id="1E4A36E81E5C564F988F90CF8610FC9F" pageId="0" pageNumber="34">• Robust, heavy-bodied marine mammals with external ear flaps, body furred except foreflippers, and hindflippers that rotate forward to enable walking; adult males 1-5-2 times longer and 3-6 times heavier than adult females.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
